SIMPLE: pucker
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pucker
<hw>Puck"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Puckered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Puckering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Poke</er> a
pocket, small bag.]</ety> <def>To gather into small folds or wrinkles;
to contract into ridges and furrows; to corrugate; -- often with
<xex>up</xex>; <as>as, to <ex>pucker</ex> up the mouth</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧His skin [was] <xex>puckered</xex> up in wrinkles.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pucker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pucker
<hw>Puck"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fold; a wrinkle; a
collection of folds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state of perplexity or anxiety; confusion; bother;
agitation.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puckerer</ent>⟦br⟧
